base for more meals rather than just toast. 
- it can ALWAYS be added as a side, especially with any meal that has a sauce component. (you can even use it to make really fast/cheap garlic bread as an accompaniment)

- if you like french toast -- make it as a treat at the end of the week with any leftover bread (french toast can also be frozen and reheated in a toaster later, for meal prepped breakfasts)
- during weeks where you have a loaf of bread, consider using it as your carb+

stored in an airtight container, it can last quite a while

- sandwiches, depending on filling, can also keep in the freezer. this can be a really nice "side" to another meal

- using the same method, you can make your own croutons. as long as the bread gets really dry in the oven and its+
